physical_examinations.vital_signs: Serum alanine aminotransferase concentration was 850 U per liter.
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Ulcer approximately 5 cm by 9 cm with a relatively clean surface and vascular granulation tissue along the border, marked periosteal reaction indicating possible osteomyelitis.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: The ulcer had been present for more than a year and had become increasingly painful during the previous few weeks.
